  <div id="navstruct">
    <h2 style="clear:both;padding-bottom:10px; padding-top:55px;" class="text-center">Navigation and Structure</h2>
    <div>
      <img class="img-m img-fluid img-right d-none d-lg-block d-xl-block" src="/images/review/img1.png"/>
      <div class="text-left">
        <p class="text-m">
          <img class="img-m img-fluid img-right d-block d-lg-none" src="/images/review/img1.png" />
          Navigation is consistent but poorly presented and somewhat effective. Navigation is consistent due to navigational bar being present in same shape throughout the website and even when scrolling down it will still persist on the top of the browser. What makes it poorly presented is because of the change in the background color of some parts of the navigational bar while on start page on top and if scrolled down it will change from transparent to opaque which it feels more like a bug rather a feature. What I don’t find effective is that they break down the menu into departments and not what is conventionally known as categories. I noticed same as some other websites the search box has dropdown to select search in certain category which I don’t know how efficient that is. Other then that the layout seems to be in order, having a carousel banner on full width of the page with featuring items, next row with three columns of useful information, followed by two rows shop by category and plus other rows of top trends and features.<br/>
          <a href="#top">Go to Top</a>
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div id="design">
    <h2 style="clear:both;padding-bottom:10px; padding-top:55px;" class="text-center" id="d">Design</h2>
    <div >
      <img class="img-m img-fluid img-left d-none d-lg-block d-xl-block" src="/images/review/img2.png"/>
      <div class="text-right">
        <p class="text-m">
          <img class="img-m img-fluid img-left d-block d-lg-none" src="/images/review/img2.png" />
          The website is quite responsive and the layout collapses accordingly to fill the content on the page. A row that has three columns will gracefully collapse into two then one column to make content readable and accessible even on smaller screens. The color scheme is simple bold dark blue for nav bar and white background for the rest of the website makes a clean view with pleasant accent. The size of the images scales properly to fill the view area designated to the item. The advertising is limited therefore distraction is not significant. There is Feedback widget, which is like sticking out tab on the left lower side and it doesn’t seem to be intrusive. Clicking on it displays a pop out window to rate and leave experience feedback.<br />
          <a href="#top">Go to Top</a>
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div id="content">
    <h2 style="clear:both;padding-bottom:5px; padding-top:55px;" class="text-center">Content</h2>
