        <p class="text-m">
          <img class="img-m img-fluid img-right d-block d-lg-none" src="/images/review/img5.png" />
          I’m not sure what is the reasoning behind it but when changing the screen size to small screen two out of four links will disappear from the navigation bar. One of those links is “Account” which I believe is very important for the users. I would redesign to make sure the users do not loose their direct access to the features of their account. And secondly, I would revise the menu to break down into categories rather departments. Departments of the store might be familiar to a permanent shopper but for occasional visitor it could be less helpful.<br />
